modules.description: This module defines a set of performance counter types for low-level system metrics, such as CPU cycles, cache misses, and context switches. It provides direct conversions between these types and string representations. Useful for profiling and performance monitoring tools that interface with hardware counters.

This module defines performance event attributes with configurable flags and types, including support for enabling/disabling counters and excluding specific execution contexts. It works with performance counter kinds like CPU cycles or cache misses, providing precise control over measurement scope. Used to configure low-level profiling events for system performance analysis.

This module implements performance event counters with precise configuration options for system-level profiling. It supports operations to create, read, reset, enable, and disable counters for specific performance metrics like CPU cycles or cache misses, using attributes and flags to control measurement scope and behavior. Concrete use cases include monitoring application performance during execution, analyzing resource usage in containers, and gathering low-level system metrics for profiling tools.
